</h3><p class="sc-kHOZwM oQMan pf-34_ pf-text-1" data-pf-type="Paragraph3">In the UK, various legislations and regulations mandate the availability and use of first aid procedures in the workplace:











</p><ul style="--pf-line-spacing-xs:10px;--pf-line-spacing-sm:10px;--pf-line-spacing-md:10px;--pf-line-spacing-lg:10px;--pf-text-indent-xs:0px;--pf-text-indent-sm:0px;--pf-text-indent-md:0px;--pf-text-indent-lg:0px" data-pf-type="List2" class="sc-kYHfwS lkFAWj pf-36_"><li data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-xiLah hUMvDY pf-37_ pf-text-1">The Health and Safety (First Aid) Regulations 1981 require employers to provide adequate and appropriate equipment, facilities, and personnel to ensure employees receive immediate attention if they are injured or taken ill at work.





















</li><li data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-xiLah hUMvDY pf-39_ pf-text-1">The Resuscitation Council (UK) provides guidelines that are widely accepted as the standard for clinical practice in relation to resuscitation.




















